---
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Bio | Tianzhichao (Tim) Hou</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Biography of Tianzhichao (Tim) Hou, MD, PhD."
    />
  </head>

  <body>
    <Header />

    <main class="bio-page">
      <section class="bio-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Bio</p>
        <h1>Tianzhichao (Tim) Hou, MD, PhD</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Physician-scientist in pediatrics, human genetics, cardiometabolic disease,
          and cancer genomics.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="bio-content">
        <h2>About</h2>
        <p>
          Tianzhichao (Tim) Hou, MD, PhD, is a physician-scientist and pediatric
          resident at Boston Children’s Hospital / Harvard Medical School. His
          academic interests lie at the intersection of pediatrics, human genetics,
          cardiometabolic disease, and cancer genomics.
        </p>

        <h2>Training and Background</h2>
        <p>
          Tim completed his medical training at Zhejiang University and pursued
          doctoral research in genetic epidemiology through Shanghai Jiao Tong
          University and the University of Toronto. His research uses population-scale
          genomic data, polygenic risk scores, Mendelian randomization, and multi-omics
          approaches to understand human disease risk, prognosis, and translational
          opportunities.
        </p>

        <h2>Research Focus</h2>
        <p>
          His work spans pediatric genetics, metabolic disease, cardiovascular risk,
          and cancer genomics. He is particularly interested in how inherited genetic
          variation can inform clinical risk prediction, disease classification, and
          individualized care.
        </p>

        <h2>Long-term Vision</h2>
        <p>
          As a physician-scientist in training, Tim aims to bridge bedside observations
          with genomic discovery, bringing human genetics closer to clinical
          decision-making in pediatrics and translational medicine.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  body {
    margin: 0;
    background: #f5f5f7;
    color: #111827;
    font-family:
      Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,
      "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
  }

  .bio-page {
    padding: 6rem 6vw;
  }

  .bio-hero {
    max-width: 980px;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: #0071e3;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .bio-hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6.5rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.06em;
  }

  .lead {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2vw, 1.6rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .bio-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    border-radius: 36px;
    background: white;
    box-shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
  }

  .bio-content h2 {
    margin: 2rem 0 0.8rem;
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .bio-content h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .bio-content p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #4b5563;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
</style>